p.s. my python solution might skip a sneaky edge case, but I think it's solid... no graphs: just check if there is a way past each 0 (edit: I think it does miss an edge case...ah well :) )

def search(d):
    for i in range(len(d)):
        if d[i]=='0':
            c=0
            for j in range(i):
                if int(d[j])>i-j:c+=1
            if c==0: return i
    return len(d)-1
print(search(input()))
